<item>
            <title>[SOLR-452] Allow for merging of contiguous fragments</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-452</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lucene&apos;s highlighter capability allows for the merging of contiguous fragments.  Currently, Solr has this hard-coded to false.  The patch to follow changes this behavior to allow it to be set in the solrconfig.xml highlighter section.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be handled via:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;int name=&quot;hl.mergeContiguous&quot;&amp;gt;true&amp;lt;/int&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The default value is false, as is the current way of doing it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
